722721f-a.title: Manhattan: Riverside Drive - 85th Street
722721f-a.text:
Riverside Drive, north from West 85th Street, showing prominently
a predecessor of the present (1937) Fifth Ave. busses. On the right is
the Misses Ely's School for Young Ladies which was formerly the Episcopal
Home of Mercy and occupying a setback position from the building line,
between 85th and 86th Streets. North of same appears a row of brick homes,
from 85th to 87th Streets.
About 1905.
MAY RE REPRODUCED.
